The first two of 12 schoolboys trapped in a flooded cave in Thailand have reportedly been brought out "alive and well" after divers executed a carefully constructed rescue mission Rising waters, falling oxygen levels and no easy way out. It’s a treacherous situation for anyone, especially 12 children and their football coach who have been trapped in a cave in Thailand. READ MORE: Thai youth football team trapped in flooded cave It’s a story that has gripped the attention of much of the world. And on Sunday, two of the trapped boys were successfully rescued and taken to a nearby hospital for treatment. Elite divers guided the boys through hours of walking, crawling, and swimming with an oxygen tank, out of a deep cave complex. READ MORE: Thai cave boys: Found alive and in good health The teammates, along with their coach, had been trapped for more than two weeks. —News24 wire